            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class=3D"quote-card">
            <div class=3D"label">Defining Quote</div>
            <blockquote>=E2=80=9CThe system did not ask what happened. It a=
sked what could be processed.=E2=80=9D</blockquote>
            <p>
              A literary memoir in conversation with works that examine mem=
ory, family systems, power inside intimacy, and the unstable boundary betwe=
en narrative and record.
            </p>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id=3D"about">
      <div class=3D"wrap cards-3">
        <article class=3D"panel">
          <div class=3D"eyebrow">About the Memoir</div>
          <h3>What the book does</h3>
          <p>
            <span class=3D"lede">Paper Walls: The Architecture of Control i=
s a literary memoir about growing up inside a family system where image gov=
erned belonging, narrative determined reality, and truth became legible onl=
y through record.</span>
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class=3D"panel">
          <div class=3D"eyebrow">Core Premise</div>
          <h3>What is at stake</h3>
          <p>
            This work examines how concern becomes story, story becomes ver=
ification, and verification becomes enforcement=E2=80=94revealing how priva=
te authority can organize perception, memory, and outcome without ever nami=
ng itself as control.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class=3D"panel">
          <div class=3D"eyebrow">What Makes It Distinct</div>
          <h3>Why it stands apart</h3>
          <p>
            Rather than asking only what happened, the memoir asks how what=
 happened was framed, stabilized, and made official=E2=80=94shifting the st=
ory from family conflict to the architecture of authority itself.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class=3D"wrap cards-mixed">
        <article class=3D"panel">
          <div class=3D"eyebrow">One-Sentence Pitch</div>
          <h2>A woman raised in a family where narrative determined authori=
ty must unravel the system that defined reality when her own life becomes t=
he next story rewritten.</h2>
          <div class=3D"stat-grid">
            <div class=3D"mini">
              <strong>Themes</strong>
              Image over interior. Performance over protection. Access over=
 intimacy. Documentation over relationship. Record over narrative.
            </div>
            <div class=3D"mini">
              <strong>Positioning</strong>
              A literary memoir examining how private authority reorganizes=
 truth inside families=E2=80=94and what it takes to step outside the struct=
ure.
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <aside class=3D"panel">
          <div class=3D"eyebrow">Author</div>
          <h3>Hsin-Neh Rogers</h3>
          <p>
            Hsin-Neh Rogers teaches in Los Angeles and serves as Adjunct Fa=
culty at Bakersfield College. Her work centers narrative control, family sy=
stems, race, documentation, and the cost of reclaiming perception.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"mini" style=3D"margin-top:18px;">
            <strong>Public-facing use</strong>
            This page functions as a clean overview of the memoir, its lang=
uage, its positioning, and its central concerns.
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id=3D"agents">
      <div class=3D"wrap panel">
        <div class=3D"eyebrow">For Agents &amp; Editors</div>
        <h2>Submission Overview</h2>
        <div class=3D"cards-2" style=3D"margin-top:22px;">
          <div class=3D"mini">
            <strong>Logline</strong>
            A woman raised in a family where narrative determined authority=
 must unravel the system that defined reality when her own life becomes the=
 next story rewritten.
          </div>
          <div class=3D"mini">
            <strong>Comps</strong>
            In conversation with <em>The Liars=E2=80=99 Club</em> (memory a=
