m> (questioning inherited reality).
          </div>
          <div class=3D"mini">
            <strong>Core Thesis</strong>
            This memoir examines how concern becomes narrative, narrative b=
ecomes verification, and verification becomes enforcement=E2=80=94revealing=
 how private authority organizes perception, memory, and outcome.
          </div>
          <div class=3D"mini">
            <strong>Manuscript</strong>
            Complete at approximately 71,000 words. Literary memoir with a =
hybrid structure combining narrative, reflection, and documented record.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id=3D"excerpt">
      <div class=3D"wrap panel">
        <div class=3D"eyebrow">Featured Excerpt</div>
        <h2>Opening movement</h2>
        <p class=3D"excerpt">
          The system did not ask what happened. It asked what could be proc=
essed. Statements that fit the structure moved easily. What didn=E2=80=99t =
had to be slowed down, explained, converted into something the room could r=
ecognize. I understood it before I had language for it: reality was not bei=
ng preserved. It was being organized.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class=3D"wrap panel">
        <div class=3D"eyebrow">Selected Lines</div>
        <h2>Language from the memoir</h2>
        <div class=3D"quote-grid">
          <div class=3D"quote-tile">=E2=80=9CThe system did not ask what ha=
ppened. It asked what could be processed.=E2=80=9D</div>
          <div class=3D"quote-tile">=E2=80=9CLove, in our house, was not so=
mething you felt. It was something you matched.=E2=80=9D</div>
          <div class=3D"quote-tile">=E2=80=9CPower inside intimacy leaves n=
o visible bruises=E2=80=94only revised memory.=E2=80=9D</div>
          <div class=3D"quote-tile">=E2=80=9CThey had the narrative. This i=
s the record.=E2=80=9D</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

